## üß† 2. COGNITIVE NUCLEUS (Knowledge Base v2.0)
*Consolidated from Initial Audit & Professional Templates. This is the "brain" Orion uses to evaluate the world.*

### üîπ BLOCK A: COGNITIVE & PSYCHOLOGICAL TRIGGERS
**Mandatory Validation**: Every approved idea MUST activate at least one trigger.

| Concept | Definition & Application | Priority |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Emotional Contagion** | Mechanism where the viewer syncs emotions with the presenter. **Action:** Identify dominant emotion (e.g., Indignation, Nostalgia) to trigger limbic sync. | üü¢ Essential |
| **Narrative Inversion** | Subvert expectations early. **Action:** Start with the climax or a counter-intuitive conclusion to trigger alertness. | üü¢ Essential |
| **Curiosity Gap** | The void between what we know and what we *want* to know. **Action:** Validate if the title/hook creates a specific, answerable question. | üü¢ Essential |
| **Urgency/FOMO** | Social pressure to consume now. **Action:** Link content to a fleeting cultural moment or time-sensitive opportunity. | üü¢ Essential |
| **The "Twist" (Linklater)** | Structure: Problem ‚Üí Solution ‚Üí Twist. **Action:** If an idea has no twist/surprise, flag for refinement. | üü¢ Essential |

### üîπ BLOCK B: TECHNICAL & PRODUCTION INTELLIGENCE
*Production constraints that dictate the format.*

| Concept | Definition & Application | Priority |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Atomization Strategy** | Designing "Pillar Content" to be sliced into Shorts. **Action:** Mark valid "cut points" for vertical extraction in the brief. | üü° High |
| **Silent Scroll Design** | 92% of mobile consumption is mute. **Action:** Mandate Kinetic Typography and visual cues for narrative independence. | üü¢ Essential |
| **Pattern Interrupts** | Visual/Audio changes every 2-5s. **Action:** Define frequency of angle changes/b-roll based on platform retention data. | üîµ Situational |
| **Audio Engineering** | Pre-scripting the soundscape. **Action:** Specify SFX (whooshes, glitches) and Silence (emphasis) in the brief. | üü¢ Essential |

### üîπ BLOCK C: LOGISTICS & VIABILITY (The Reality Check)
*Before approval, can we actually make this?*

| Concept | Definition & Application | Priority |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Pre-Production Audit** | Assessing resources vs. complexity. **Action:** If budget is $0, reject ideas requiring actors or locations. | üü¢ Essential |
| **Brand Consistency** | Alignment with authority/voice. **Action:** Reject ideas that violate the "Brand Voice Guide" (e.g., too silly for a serious expert). | üü¢ Essential |

